<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="O" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Opposite1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Opposite,</orth> subst. 1) adversary: <bibl n="shak. mm 3.2.175" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. III, 2, 175</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 3.2.68" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. III, 2, 68</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 3.4.253" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 4, 253</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 3.4.253" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 4, 253</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 1.3.55" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B I, 3, 55</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.1.16" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 16</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 5.3.22" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B V, 3, 22</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 5.4.3" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 V, 4, 3</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 2.2.23" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. II, 2, 23</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 5.2.62" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. V, 2, 62</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 5.3.42" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. V, 3, 42</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 5.3.42" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. V, 3, 42</bibl><lb />2) contrary: <cit><quote>just o. to what thou justly seemest,</quote> <bibl n="shak. rom 3.2.78" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. III, 2, 78</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>each o. that blanks the face of joy meet what I would have well and it destroy,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 3.2.230" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. III, 2, 230</bibl></cit> (or == contrariety?). <cit><quote>the present pleasure, by revolution lowering, does become the o. of itself,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ant 1.2.130" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. I, 2, 130</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>